  "informal_statement": "For every function f : alpha -> beta and sets s, t : Set beta: the preimage of the intersection f^-1(s inter t) equals the intersection of the preimages f^-1(s) inter f^-1(t).",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Cited directly via Mathlib's Set.preimage_inter. Preimage counterpart to the already-landed image_union packet.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem preimage_inter {α β : Type*} (f : α → β) (s t : Set β) : f ⁻¹' (s ∩ t) = f ⁻¹' s ∩ f ⁻¹' t",
